    "encrypted": "false",
    "display_name": "Scenario 1",
    "long_instructions": "*Review the scenario below and use the AI Chat to learn more in-depth about this threat:*\r\n\r\n## Scenario 1\r\n\r\nYou receive an email from a classmate with a link that says, “Click here for 1000 free Fortnite v-bucks!”. \r\n\r\nYou click the link and it downloads a file to your computer — hmmm, that was unexpected. Instead of giving you free v-bucks, the file you downloaded automatically sends the same fake email to everyone in your contacts list, making it look like you sent it! \r\n\r\nThe malicious file spreads to dozens of students, slowing devices and potentially stealing passwords.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/351687e403fac3c115b85fea72a6cb9d-image-1752764017862.jpg\" alt=\"emails and virus particles being sent digitally\" width=\"300\"/>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Chat with an Expert: Malware Analyst\r\n\r\nA **malware analyst** studies malicious software to understand how it works, how it spreads, and how to remove it.\r\n",
